> (i.i.d.). This requirement can be weakened; convergence of the mean to th=
e normal distribution also occurs for non-identical distributions or for no=
n-independent observations if they comply with certain conditions.
</p><p>The earliest version of this theorem, that the normal distribution m=
ay be used as an approximation to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Binomial_distribution" title=3D"Binomial distribution">binomial distrib=
ution</a>, is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/De_Moivre%E2%80%=
93Laplace_theorem" title=3D"De Moivre=E2=80=93Laplace theorem">de Moivre=E2=
=80=93Laplace theorem</a>.
</p>
