<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"The_generalized_central_lim=
it_theorem">The generalized central limit theorem</h2><span class=3D"mw-edi=
tsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCentral_limit_theorem&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: The generalized central limit th=
eorem"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></div>
<p>The generalized central limit theorem (GCLT) was an effort of multiple m=
athematicians (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sergei_Natanovich_B=
ernstein" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sergei Natanovich Bernstein">Berns=
tein</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jarl_Waldemar_Lindeberg"=
 title=3D"Jarl Waldemar Lindeberg">Lindeberg</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Paul_L%C3%A9vy_(mathematician)" title=3D"Paul L=C3=A9vy (ma=
thematician)">L=C3=A9vy</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willi=
am_Feller" title=3D"William Feller">Feller</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Andrey_Kolmogorov" title=3D"Andrey Kolmogorov">Kolmogorov</a>=
, and others) over the period from 1920 to 1937.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_limit_the=
orem#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The first published complete proof of the GC=
LT was in 1937 by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_L%C3%A9vy_(=
mathematician)" title=3D"Paul L=C3=A9vy (mathematician)">Paul L=C3=A9vy</a>=
 in French.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_limit_theorem#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> An Eng=
lish language version of the complete proof of the GCLT is available in the=
 translation of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Vladimirovic=
h_Gnedenko" title=3D"Boris Vladimirovich Gnedenko">Gnedenko</a> and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrey_Kolmogorov" title=3D"Andrey Kolmog=
orov">Kolmogorov</a>'s 1954 book.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_limit_theorem#cite_note-=
14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p><p>The statement of the GCLT is as follows:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_limit_theo=
rem#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><i>A non-degenerate random variable</i> <i>Z</i> <i>is <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stable_distribution" title=3D"Stable distribut=
ion"><i>=CE=B1</i>-stable</a> for some</i> 0 &lt; <i>=CE=B1</i> =E2=89=A4 2=
 <i>if and only if there is an independent, identically distributed sequenc=
e of random variables</i> <i>X</i><sub>1</sub>, <i>X</i><sub>2</sub>, <i>X<=
/i><sub>3</sub>, <i>... and constants</i> <i>a</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> &gt; =
0, <i>b</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> =E2=88=88 =E2=84=9D <i>with</i></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><i>a</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> (<i>X</i><sub>1</sub> + ... + <=
i>X</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>) =E2=88=92 <i>b</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> =E2=86=92=
 <i>Z</i>.</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><i>Here =E2=86=92 means the sequence of random variable sums conver=
ges in distribution; i.e., the corresponding distributions satisfy</i> <i>F=
</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>(<i>y</i>) =E2=86=92 <i>F</i>(<i>y</i>) <i>at all co=
ntinuity points of</i> <i>F.</i></dd></dl>
<p>In other words, if sums of independent, identically distributed random v=
ariables converge in distribution to some <i>Z</i>, then <i>Z</i> must be a=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stable_distribution" title=3D"Sta=
ble distribution">stable distribution</a>.
</p>
