<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Convergence_to_the_limit">C=
onvergence to the limit</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DCentral_limit_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D13" title=
=3D"Edit section: Convergence to the limit"><span>edit</span></a><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The central limit theorem gives only an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Asymptotic_distribution" title=3D"Asymptotic distribution">asympto=
tic distribution</a>. As an approximation for a finite number of observatio=
ns, it provides a reasonable approximation only when close to the peak of t=
he normal distribution; it requires a very large number of observations to =
stretch into the tails.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact"=
 style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=
=3D"Not immediately obvious, I didn't find a source via google (July 2016)"=
>citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p>The convergence in the central limit theorem is <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_convergence" title=3D"Uniform convergence">uni=
form</a> because the limiting cumulative distribution function is continuou=
s. If the third central <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moment_(ma=
thematics)" title=3D"Moment (mathematics)">moment</a> <span class=3D"mwe-ma=
th-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline m=
we-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.=
org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle \operatorname {E} \left[(X_{1}=
-\mu )^{3}\right]}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">E</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>[</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
            <msub>
              <mi>X</mi>
